data.chText: 那一家唯一在世的成员
data.enText: the sole surviving member of the family

data.chText: 我到这儿唯一的原因就是来看你。
data.enText: My sole reason for coming here was to see you.

data.chText: 这是这栋建筑物唯一的入口。
data.enText: This is the sole means of access to the building.

data.chText: 独占的；专有的；全权处理的
data.enText: belonging to one person or group; not shared

data.chText: 那个项目由她一人负责。
data.enText: She has sole responsibility for the project.
the bottom surface of the foot

data.chText: 灼热的沙地使他们的脚掌感到火辣辣的。
data.enText: The hot sand burned the soles of their feet .
the bottom part of a shoe or sock, not including the heel
having the type of soles mentioned
a flat sea fish that is used for food
to repair a shoe by replacing the sole

tr: most common in warm seas especially European
the underside of footwear or a golf club
lean flesh of any of several flatfish

value.def: The sole thing or person of a particular type is the only one of that type.

example.ex: Their sole aim is to destabilize the Indian government.
example.tran: 他们唯一的目的就是要动摇印度政府的统治。

value.def: If you have sole charge or ownership of something, you are the only person in charge of it or who owns it.

example.ex: Many women are left as the sole providers in families after their husband has died...
example.tran: 许多女人在丈夫去世之后只好独自供养一家人。

example.ex: Chief Hart had sole control over that fund.
example.tran: 哈特主任独自掌控那笔资金。

value.tran: (控制权或所有权)唯一的，独占的

value.def: The sole of your foot or of a shoe or sock is the underneath surface of it.

example.ex: He had burned the sole of his foot.
example.tran: 他的一只脚脚底被灼伤了。

value.def: A sole is a kind of flat fish that you can eat.

posc.def: Sole is this fish eaten as food.
